(1000, 20, 33, 512, 'Bhimbetka Caves', 'Bhimbetka is known for more than 12,000 years old rock shelters lying in the Raisen district of Madhya Pradesh, 45 km south of Bhopal. Bhimbetka rock shelters lie at the Southern edge of the Vindhyachal hills and the site is spread over 10 km in length and about 3 km in width.\r\nBhimbetka rock shelters are a UNESCO world heritage site and are known as the earliest traces of human life in India. Some of the Stone Age rock paintings found among the Bhimbetka rock shelters are approx. 30,000 yrs old. Bhimbetka got its name from the Mahabharata character Bhima, as Bhimbetka means "sitting place of Bhima".\r\n\r\nRaisen is also known for the shrine of Hazrat Peer Fatehullah Shah Baba who was a well known Muslim Saint. The people in and around Raisen have great faith in the shrine and it is believed that the shrine can fulfill the desires of pilgrims. The origin of Raisen fort can be dated back to 1200 A.D. Raisen fort has been under the rules of various rulers.\r\n', '1468397532Bhimbetka Caves1.jpg', '1468397532Bhimbetka Caves2.jpg'),
(1001, 20, 33, 503, 'Islamnagar', 'Islamnagar is a palace, that was built by Dost Mohammed Khan as a love nest close to Bhopal. Tourists will find the palace of Islam nagar to be a luxurious one, surrounded by beautiful gardens. Tourists can find a mixture of Hindu and Islamic architecture and artwork in the palace.\r\nThe two other monuments worth visiting in Islamnagar are the Chaman Mahal and the Rani Mahal. Chaman Mahal is a palace that is surrounded on all sides by lovely gardens (Chaman in Urdu means garden). Chaman palace also houses a hamam (bath) for the use of royalty, which is accessible to the tourists. A Sheesh Mahal near the doorway complemented the Hammam, however, the Sheesh Mahal is closed for travellers.\r\nRight next to the Chaman Mahal lies the two storied Rani Mahal that was the living palace of the queens who accompanied the royal men during their vacations. It is a rectangular building with deep arches. It has a beautiful baradari inside.\r\n', '1468397589Islamnagar1.jpg', '1468397589Islamnagar2.jpg'),
(1002, 20, 33, 514, 'Kerwan Dam', 'Kerwan Dam, 17 km from Bhopal off Kotra Sultanabad road, is a beautiful picnic spot surrounded by hills and full of greenery.', '1468397889Kerwan Dam1.jpg', '1468397889Kerwan Dam2.jpg'),
(1003, 20, 33, 503, 'Raisen Fort', 'Raisen is 23 kms from Bhopal, and is known for the Raisen fort and the Durgah of Raisen. Raisen fort is situated on the top of a hill with a few temples, palaces, a large water reservoir and numerous wells inside Raisen fort. There is a temple and mosque in the same complex of Raisen fort. Raisen fort had many domes inside, however, only two of them are left which are now abode of Bats.', '1468397929Raisen Fort1.jpg', '1468397929Raisen Fort2.jpg'),
(1004, 20, 33, 503, 'Sanchi', 'Sanchi is a small village situated in the Raisen district of Madhya Pradesh, located 46 km north east of Bhopal. Sanchi is a serene hill home to several of amazing Buddhist monuments dating from 3rd century BC to 12th century AD. Sanchi is an important Buddhist pilgrimage centre and is frequented by numerous tourists all round the year.\r\nThe Great Stupa at Sanchi is the oldest stone structure in India, which was commissioned by the emperor Ashoka in 3rd century BC. The main part of the Stupa at Sanchi is a hemispherical brick structure built over the relics of Buddha. There is also a balustrade encircling the brick structure with four carved ornamental gateways.\r\nMore stupas and structures were built over the following period till the 12th century CE. The structures of Sanchi later fell in disrepair after the decline of Buddhism in India.\r\n', '1468398020Sachi1.jpg', '1468398020Sachi2.jpg'),
(1005, 20, 33, 503, 'Ginnorgarh Fort', 'Ginnorgarh is a historical fort that is situated on an isolated hill about 1127 m high and 266 m broad. Ginnorgarh fort is around 65 km from Bhopal and 3 km from Delawadi. Tourists can avail buses till Delawadi from Bhopal and then have to walk on foot to reach Ginnorgarh. The fort of Ginnorgarh was once a stronghold of Gonds, but fell to Dost Mohammad of Bhopal State', '1468398049Ginnorgarh Fort1.jpg', '1468398049Ginnorgarh Fort2.jpg'),
(1006, 20, 34, 503, 'Tansen Tomb', 'The father of Hindustani classical music and one of the nine jewels of Akbar court, legendary singer Tansen is buried in Gwalior. Built in the early style of Mughal architecture, the tomb of Tansen has a simple and pristine aura about it.\r\nThe headstone is surrounded by beautiful gardens on all its sides. Apart from being an ancient monument, the site also underlines the rich cultural heritage of Gwalior. Every year in the month of November/ December, a national level music competition is held at the place, to venerate this great musician.\r\n', '1468398154Tansen1.jpg', '1468398154Tansen2.jpg'),
(1007, 20, 34, 503, 'Gwalior Fort', 'Gwalior Fort, described as the pearl in the necklace of the castles of Hind by the Mughal Emperor Babur, is the pride of Madhya Pradesh. Situated at 91m higher than the city and sorrounded by 9m high wall, the majestic Gwalior fort is one of the largest and the mightiest forts in India.', '1468398234Gwalior Fort images1.jpg', '1468398234Gwalior Fort images2.jpg'),
(1008, 20, 34, 510, 'Khajuraho Erotic Temples', 'If you want proof that the Kama Sutra originated in India, Khajuraho is the place to see. Erotica abounds here with over 20 temples devoted to sexuality and sex. These sandstone temples, which date back to the 10th and 11th century, are the only ones remaining out of 85 temples constructed during this time. The aerial distance from Gwalior to Khajuraho is 233 km while the road distance between Gwalior toKhajuraho is 278 km.By Train it is 298 Km.\r\nThere are 3 groups of temples -- Western, Eastern, and Southern. The main temples are in the Western group, which features the magnificent Kandariya Mahadeo Temple. The Eastern Group contains a number of exquisitely sculptured Jain temples. There are only two temples in the Southern group.\r\n', '1468398289Khajuraho1.jpg', '1468398289Khajuraho2.jpg'),
(1009, 20, 35, 505, 'Rani Durgavati Memorial and Museum', 'Rani Durgavati Museum in Jabalpur of the great Queen Durgavati, contains a fine collection of sculptures, inscriptions and prehistoric relics. The museum is open for tourists from Tuesday to Sunday from 10.00AM to 5.00PM.', '1468398372Rani Durgavati Memorial and Museum1.jpg', '1468398372Rani Durgavati Memorial and Museum2.jpg'),
(1010, 20, 35, 503, 'Madan Mahal Fort', 'Built on 11th century by Gond ruler, Raja Madanshah, this fort is a pride of Jabalpur city. Madan Mahal fort is built on top of a rocky hill and visible from most of the parts of Jabalpur city. Jabalpur is also famous for eroded volcanic rock formations called as Balancing Rock of Jabalpur (on the way to Madan Mahal Fort). Amazingly this rock survived even in earthquake of mag 6.5.', '1468398427Madan Mahal Fort1.jpg', '1468398427Madan Mahal Fort2.jpg'),
(1011, 20, 35, 515, 'Bhedaghat and Dhuandhar', 'Just 20 km from Jabalpur, Bhedaghat is a marvelous site where tourists can enjoy the beauty of the perpendicular Marble Rocks that fringe the crystal clear placid waters of Narmada River.\r\nAbout 20 km from Jabalpur and at a little distance from Bhedaghat, there is a water fall known as â€˜Dhuandharâ€™ where droplets of water at the fall rise in a massive way, creating the illusion of vapors so powerful that travellers can hear its roar from a large distance.\r\n', '1468398513Bhedaghat and Dhuandhar1.jpg', '1468398513Bhedaghat and Dhuandhar2.jpg'),
(1012, 20, 36, 515, 'Rajat Prapat (Big Fall)', 'Rajat Prapat also known as Big Fall, about 1 km away from Apsara Vihar, is a beautiful fall with a height of hundred and ten meters. The beautiful drops generated from water fall appear like shining pearls floating in the air. The fall gives a spectacular view during the rainy season.', '1468398588Raja prapat1.jpg', '1468398588Raja prapat2.jpg'),
(1013, 20, 36, 512, 'Pandava Caves', 'Pandava Caves are five ancient (around 6th to 7th Century) dwellings excavated in sandstone rock in a low hill in Pachmarhi. It is believed that Pandava caves were once occupied by the 5 Pandava brothers. These caves are now protected monuments under the archeological survey of India.', '1468398625Pandava Caves1.jpg', '1468398625Pandava Caves2.jpg'),
(1014, 20, 37, 506, 'Kanha National Park', 'Kanha National Park has the honor of providing the setting for Rudyard Kiplings classic novel, The Jungle Book. Its rich in lush saal and bamboo forests, lakes, streams and open grasslands. As well as tigers, the park abounds with barasingha (swamp deer) and an extensive variety of other animals and birds. Rather than offering one particular kind of animal, it provides an all-round nature experience. The park is well regarded for its research and conservation programs, and many endangered species have been saved there', '1468398715Kanha National park.jpg', ''),
(1015, 21, 25, 516, 'Lonawala and Khandala', 'Lonawala and Khandala both are the hill station in Pune district. Lonavala is famous throughout India for the hard candy sweet known as chikki. Lonavala has been blessed with valleys, hills, Milky WaterFalls, Lush Greenery and pleasant cool winds. Khandala has been blessed with natures beauty in abundance. The natural splendor, combined with peaceful surroundings, makes the hill station the perfect holiday spot. Today, Khandala is counted amongst one of the most visited tourist destinations in India.', '1468398864Lonavala-Khandala Hill Station1.jpg', '1468398864Lonavala-Khandala Hill Station2.jpg'),
(1016, 21, 25, 503, 'Gandhi National Memorial / Aga Khan Palace', 'Mahatma Gandhi, Kasturba Gandhi, Shri Mahadeobhai Desai, Dr. Sarojini Naidu and others were kept under imprisonment in the Agakhan Palace during 1942- Quit India movement. Shri Mahadeobhai Desai and Kasturba Gandhi breathed their last breath in this Palace. Marble memorials of these two great leaders are there. Agakhan Palace is known for its architectural excellence. Spreading on a 19-acre land, the picturesque beauty of the palace captivates the eye of every onlooker, with its magnificent structure. Mahatma Gandhis items like his bed, writing desk, Kasturbas saree and other clothes, her Chappals (slippers) are maintained properly at their place.', '1468398915Gandhi National Memorial 1.jpg', '1468398915Gandhi National Memorial 2.jpg'),
(1017, 21, 26, 505, 'Coin Museum', 'The museum has a fine collection of research and well-documented history of Indian currencies. Coin Museum was established in 1980 under the Indian Institute of Research in Numismatic Studies. This museum is the only museum of its kind in Asia. The environment of the museum is so cool, as it is located in the backdrop of the enthralling Ajneri Hill of Nashik.', '1468398957Coin Museum1.jpg', '1468398957Coin Museum2.jpg'),
(1018, 21, 26, 512, 'Pandavleni Caves', 'Pandavleni caves are 2000-year-old, and it was built by the Jain Kings. It is a group of 24 Hinayana Buddhist Caves, which date back between 1st century BC and 2nd century AD. These caves are at a distance of 8 km from Nasik. Amongst all, cave number 3 and 10 are the best. Cave number 3 has a large Vihara with fascinating sculptures, cave number 10 is also a Vihara, but it is much older and finer than the cave number 3. It is believed to be as old as the Karla Cave near Lonavala', '1468398984Pandavleni Caves1.jpg', '1468398984Pandavleni Caves2.jpg'),
(1019, 21, 26, 512, 'Ajanta and Elora', 'Ajanta & Ellora Caves: Cave Hindu temples of India. In the Indian state of Maharashtra is the village of Ajanta & Ellora with incredible Temples carved into the mountain Charanandri by ancient Indian architects & engineers. Ellora â€“ the official World Heritage Site by UNESCO. The caves consist of 27 Hindu temples built during the 100BC â€“ a sign of Hindu religious harmony that has prevailed in India.', '1468399011ajanta cave1.jpg', '1468399011ajanta cave2.jpg'),
(1020, 11, 24, 510, 'Basilica of Bom Jesus', 'The Basilica of Bom Jesus or Borea Jezuchi is located in Goa, India, and is a UNESCO World Heritage Site. The basilica holds the mortal remains of St. Francis Xavier. The church is located in Old Goa, which was the capital of Goa in the early days of Portuguese rule. \r\n''Bom Jesus'' (literally, ''Good (or Holy) Jesus'') is the name used for the Ecce Homo in the countries of Portuguese colonization. The Jesuit church is Indiaâ€™s first minor basilica, and is considered to be one of the best examples of baroque architecture in India.\r\n', '1468480204Basilica of Bom Jesus.jpg', '1468480204Basilica of Bom Jesus2.jpg'),
(1021, 11, 24, 500, 'Ashwem beach ', 'Ashwem beach in north Goa is beautiful with its long beach with white sand. It is a quiet beach compared to Morjim or the others further north. It has lots of resorts nearby and is definitely a beach not to be missed while in north Goa. Perhaps, most neat, serene and secluded beach in Goa. There is not much crowd around and you can spend quality time with you family. The eateries around are also quite good. The view of sunset and sunrise is awesome.', '1468480246ashwem-beach.jpg', '1468480246Ashwem Beach2.jpg'),
(1022, 11, 24, 502, 'Deltin Royale Casino', 'As the name says, its a casino and all in a stationary ship. Many counters to play or gamble or play intelligently or gamble calculatedly. There are manual play areas and also fully automated. Good food. Nice place to spend time and money. Though the entry is expensive, it is worth the pay, the crowd inside is good, service is prompt and food is always nice.', '1468480285Deltin Royale Casino.jpg', '1468480285Deltin Royale Casino2.jpg'),
(1023, 11, 24, 510, 'Se Cathedral', 'This is one of the must visit places, if you are on your first visit to Goa. It has got a beautiful architecture and covered with splendid surroundings.\r\nIts a part of the Archeological complex consisting of church and museum and located just across the road from Bom JesusBasilica.Pretty touristy but no one bugs the tourists unlike in other spots It is also an active church with mass and prayers regularly.\r\n', '1468480373Se Cathedral.jpg', '1468480373Se Cathedral2.jpg'),
(1024, 11, 24, 515, 'Dudhsagar Falls', 'Dudhsagar Falls (literally Sea of Milk ) is a four-tiered waterfall located on the Mandovi River in the border of the Indian states ofKarnataka and Goa. It is 60 km from Panaji by road and is located on the Madgaon-Belgaum rail route about 46 km east of Madgaonand 80 km south of Belgaum. Dudhsagar Falls is amongst India''s tallest waterfalls with a height of 310 m(1017 feet) and an average width of 30 metres (100 feet).The falls is located in the Bhagwan Mahaveer Sanctuary and Mollem National Park among the Western Ghats. The waterfall forms the border between Karnataka and Goa states. The area is surrounded by a deciduous forests with a rich bio diversity. The falls are not particularly spectacular during the dry season but during the monsoon season however, the falls are fed by rains and form a huge force of water.', '1468480415dudh1.jpg', '1468480415dudh2.jpg'),
(1025, 11, 40, 500, 'Agonda Beach', 'Agonda is in the southernmost Canacona taluka of Indian state of Goa.\r\nAgonda is a great spot for sunbathing, relaxing and swimming, with still relatively few tourists. Agonda is a nice long pristine stretch of beach. Though the waters here might not be the most ideal place for swimming (you have better beaches with calm waters in Goa), Agonda is definitely a place for those who want to quit on a Monday morning.\r\n', '1468480453agonda beach.jpg', '1468480453agonda2.jpg'),
(1026, 11, 41, 503, 'Chapora Fort', 'Located in Bardez around 15km from Baga Beach. Includes a bit of trekking as well. Nice picturesque view of sea. If you are a travel buff and nature lover, this place gives you great satisfaction of the visit. The fort though ruined, became a very photogenic spot. The view of Baga river meeting the ocean is amazing.Its the place where Dil chahta hai the famous Hindi movie got shoot. It''s an awesome feeling to click a picture at the top of the fort with the sea behind you.', '1468480486chapora.jpg', '1468480486chapora2.jpg'),
(1027, 11, 41, 503, 'Chapora Fort', 'Located in Bardez around 15km from Baga Beach. Includes a bit of trekking as well. Nice picturesque view of sea. If you are a travel buff and nature lover, this place gives you great satisfaction of the visit. The fort though ruined, became a very photogenic spot. The view of Baga river meeting the ocean is amazing.Its the place where Dil chahta hai the famous Hindi movie got shoot. It''s an awesome feeling to click a picture at the top of the fort with the sea behind you.', '1468480581chapora.jpg', '1468480581chapora2.jpg'),
(1028, 12, 42, 506, 'Gir National Park and Wildlife Sanctuary', 'The Gir Forest National Park and Wildlife Sanctuary (also known as Sasan-Gir, and à¤—à¤¿à¤° à¤µà¤¨) is a forest and wildlife sanctuaryNear Talala Gir in Gujarat, India. Established in 1965, with a total area of 1,412 km2 (545 sq mi) (about 258 km2 (100 sq mi) for the fully protected area the national park and 1,153 km2 (445 sq mi) for the Sanctuary). Very rustic and natural place. However u spot a lion only if you are lucky. Generally it takes at least 2 to 3 trips for people to spot a lion.', '1468480640gir1.jpg', '1468480640gir2.jpg'),
(1029, 12, 42, 510, 'Somnath temple', 'The Somnath temple located in Prabhas Patan near Veraval in Saurashtra on the western coast of Gujarat, India, is the first among the twelve Jyotirlinga shrines of Shiva.[1] It is an important pilgrimage and tourist spot. The temple is considered sacred due to the various legends connected to it. Somnath means "Lord of the Soma", an epithet of Shiva.\r\nThe Somnath temple is known as "the Shrine Eternal".\r\nSomnath ji is an incredibly magnificient temple and Jyotirling. A very big temple scenic from outside and holyness purifies the mind and soul from all over. The mandie is surrounded by sea from two sides. Light and sound show in the evening.\r\n', '1468480670Somnath Mahadev Temple.jpg', '1468480670Somnath Mahadev Temple2.jpg'),
(1030, 12, 43, 505, 'Sabarmati Ashram', 'Located on the Sabarmati River Front this is a must see place. Very peaceful, very well maintained. The overall stress level goes down in this place. Very beautiful and a must watch in Ahmedabad. This place is very quiet. if you are interested in history and Mahatma Gandhi''s life, this is great. Many rooms are locked and many of his artifacts are still present. It gives the impression of Gandhi soul is here. A place which must be watched by everyone. On the bank of sabarmati river,it gives immense pleasure.', '1468480717Sabarmati Ashram.jpg', '1468480717Sabarmati Ashram2.jpg'),
(1031, 12, 43, 510, 'Akshardham Temple', 'Serene and peaceful are two words for this place. This place has a small museum as well which gives a glimpse to Swaminarayn''s life. No mobile or photography inside the temple. For those who are in search of peace. The temple''s architecture is truly marvelous. The Temple is very beautiful and also gives options for kids to enjoy rides. Most Interesting part is the Laser show which is a Must watch for all.', '1468480742Akshardham Temple.jpg', '1468480742Akshardham Temple2.jpg'),
(1032, 12, 43, 509, 'Sabarmati Riverfront', 'This is one of the place to must visit while your visit to Ahmedabad.Long nice stretch of Sabarmati river for walking, jogging, hanging out, photography, quick getaway. Overall nice place for a peaceful walk at morning and evening hours. On both side of sabarmati river its developed by land scape garden in selected at place. Greenery all-around and attractions like boating, eatery, playing area. Great picnic spot.', '1468480772Sabarmati Riverfront.jpg', '1468480772Sabarmati Riverfront2.jpg'),
(1033, 12, 44, 509, 'White desert', 'It''s true what they say about this place. Agar Kutch nahi dekha toh kuch nahi dekha! The rendezvous of the sunset with the white sands of the dessert is a breathtaking view and I''d lie if I said I didn''t get a little teary eyed. While the show put up by the military force on their camels is a sight. this white salt desert is also known as great rann of kutch. its the largest salt flats of the india.', '1468480829White Desert.jpg', '1468480829White Desert2.jpg'),
(1034, 12, 45, 510, 'Dwarkadhish Temple', 'Dwarka Dheesh temple is one of the Char Dhams situated in Gujarat . Near to a Backwater lake called Gomti River. Temple is nicely maintained. Surrounding areas have also been maintained to a large extent. Good hotels have come up now. Good developments have also taken place around.\r\nSoothing effect on mind and relaxing of body by even witnessing the holy Dwarkadhish ji. Sit for a while before the god and just relax. Hundreds of centuries old temple, one of the 4 Dhams of hindu mythology.\r\n', '1468480857Dwarkadhish Temple.jpg', '1468480857Dwarkadhish Temple2.jpg'),
(1035, 12, 45, 510, 'Dwarkadhish Temple', 'Dwarka Dheesh temple is one of the Char Dhams situated in Gujarat . Near to a Backwater lake called Gomti River. Temple is nicely maintained. Surrounding areas have also been maintained to a large extent. Good hotels have come up now. Good developments have also taken place around.\r\nSoothing effect on mind and relaxing of body by even witnessing the holy Dwarkadhish ji. Sit for a while before the god and just relax. Hundreds of centuries old temple, one of the 4 Dhams of hindu mythology.\r\n', '1468480917Dwarkadhish Temple.jpg', '1468480917Dwarkadhish Temple2.jpg'),
(1036, 13, 46, 517, 'Kingdom of dreams', 'It is a real Kingdom of Dreams experience, the actors, decors of the place, The attractions outside the theatre, the typical Indian cuisine food stalls. Everything was just WOW. The actors performance was wonderful and sound system inside the theatre was superb. It is a must see if someone is visiting Gurgaon. Brilliant experience! Firstly Kingdom of Dreams is an oasis in the desert. You get transported to a first world like entertainment place and professional staff. The show itself is beautifully choreographed and runs punctuallly with a Broadway like experience. ', '1468480992king.jpg', '1468480992king2.jpg'),
(1037, 13, 46, 502, 'Cyber Hub', 'if you have time to kill but not sure what to do. This is the perfect place to go from clubs to restaurants this place can give any clubbing district abroad a run for it''s money. Enjoy fine dining at restaurants that offer multiple international cuisine and Party till the night ends at one of the clubs. ', '1468481052Cyber Hub.jpg', '1468481052Cyber Hub2.jpg'),
(1038, 13, 46, 507, 'Ambience Mall', 'One of the biggest malls of Asia.The mall is very luxurious with lots of "high-end" shops, food section and entertainment section. The cinema is very luxurious there too and the shop display is just too great. Anyone could think that they were on Europe instead of India. Quality of the products are also very good.\r\nFrom a huge variety of eating options - economical to high ambience. Almost any brand available in India, is availabe here. Huge playout area for kids. Ultimate variety of daily needs - grocery shopping to luxury, spectacles to mobile covers. You can find all of it under one roof.\r\n', '1468481078Ambience Mall.jpg', '1468481078Ambience Mall2.jpg'),
(1039, 13, 47, 504, 'Brahma Sarovar', 'Considered as ancient water tank sacred in Hinduism. Water in sarovar is very clean. View was magnificent and area is quite huge. This is the place where Pandavas took a dip after the epic war, which killed all their Kaurava cousins. It has a small temple which is also quite well maintained. A sacred shrine stands within the sarover dedicated to lord Shiva.One of the largest man-made tanks, the brahmasarover is perfectly rectangular.', '1468481119brahma-sarovar.jpg', '1468481119Brahma Sarovar2.jpg'),
(1040, 13, 47, 505, 'Sri Krishna Museum', 'Museum dedicated to Shri Krishna in the same compound of Krishna Panorama and Science Centre. This place is located in the heart of the city, very well maintained. Multimedia gallery is impressive. Photography is not permitted inside. Lockers are available. Everything is perfect and magical over there, have to be there at least once in life to see the past.\r\n\r\n', '1468481146Sri Krishna Museum1.jpg', '1468481146Sri Krishna Museum2.jpg'),
(1041, 13, 47, 505, 'Sri Krishna Museum', 'Museum dedicated to Shri Krishna in the same compound of Krishna Panorama and Science Centre. This place is located in the heart of the city, very well maintained. Multimedia gallery is impressive. Photography is not permitted inside. Lockers are available. Everything is perfect and magical over there, have to be there at least once in life to see the past.\r\n\r\n', '1468481228Sri Krishna Museum1.jpg', '1468481228Sri Krishna Museum2.jpg'),
(1042, 14, 48, 510, 'Dalai Lama Temple Complex', 'A very beautiful temple of Lord Buddha. Also it depicts the tibetian culture and history of tibetian buddhism, their fight for liberty from the Chinese troops. The statue of Lord Buddha is very beautiful and charming with peaceful atmosphere.\r\nVisiting the temple brings in a different kind of inner peace and one feels blessed. Very serene and humbling experience.\r\n', '1468481257Dalai Lama Temple Complex.jpg', '1468481257Dalai Lama Temple Complex2.jpg'),
(1043, 14, 48, 509, 'HPCA Stadium', 'You love cricket or not, you must visit this stadium to view it''s beauty. Small ground, everything is so easily visible, colors everywhere, cool atmosphere, so beautifully maintained. Best is Hills at back.. Nature at its best.\r\nA stadium at highest level in India. A cricket fan will love to visit this place.you can take selfies with stadium background.\r\n', '1468481303HPCA Stadium.jpg', '1468481303HPCA Stadium2.jpg'),
(1044, 14, 48, 515, 'Bhagsu Waterfall', 'The experience in this waterfall was not less than pouring ice cold water on yourself continuously. It took around one hour of walk from Mcleodganj main square to waterfall. It has proper road approx one km before the waterfall, after that its small path but still properly managed. Visiting this place is a must if you are visiting mcleodganj.', '1468481327Bhagsu Waterfall.jpg', '1468481327Bhagsu Waterfall2.jpg'),
(1045, 14, 49, 510, 'Manki Point - Hanuman Temple', 'Manki point is situated in the Air Force Station complex. It is situated 4 km from the bus stand. The place is linked to the mythological event when Lord Hanuman was travelling to get the Sanjeevni Booti and placed his foot on a mountaintop to rest and propel himself up again. The mountaintop got flattened and became a temple. The place is caused Manki point as locals believe that whatever you wish for will come true. ', '1468481362Manki Point - Hanuman Temple.jpg', '1468481362Manki Point - Hanuman Temple2.jpg'),
(1046, 14, 50, 504, 'Chamera Lake', 'Excellent Experience. Superb. Do not miss it. Just 8 minutes ride but ...it is PURE thrill and fun. The staff is very lively and will help you take all kind of pics and videos.It is a nice place for water loving people. speed boats and motor boats are available. ', '1468481386Chamera Lake.jpg', '1468481386Chamera Lake2.jpg'),
(1047, 14, 50, 504, 'Khajjiar Lake', 'No amount of words can describe the beauty of this place. Its out of the world. One of the best location in India. Just an hour drive from dalhousie. the best time to visit is monsoon (July-Aug) which adds icing on the cake. The way to this place is equally beutiful and picturesque. ', '1468481417Khajjiar Lake.jpg', '1468481417Khajjiar Lake2.jpg'),
(1048, 14, 51, 504, 'Beas River', 'The best part of travelling to Manali or Rohtang is the Beas river. Its absolutely amazing to watch the river flowing one side and hills on the other while travelling. It offers spectacular views of the hills and the sound of gushing water is a music to the ears. If you are in Manali, make sure you stop by the river for a couple of hours to soak in the beauty and bounty of nature. The clear gurgling water, spectacular backdrop, absolute serenity is sure to calm your senses.', '1468481443Beas River.jpg', '1468481443Beas River2.jpg'),
(1049, 14, 51, 501, 'Rohtang Pass', 'mother nature is at its best all along the 54kms and even beyond. Be it snow peak mountains, or marvelous mountain shapes or waterfalls coming from nowhere. Donâ€™t miss it if you stay in Manali, it will only take a couple of hoursâ€™ drive up for 50+km, but the views are stunning and the entire experience rewarding. Stop along the way as many times as you wish to enjoy the panorama.', '1468481478Rohtang Pass.jpg', '1468481478Rohtang Pass2.jpg'),
(1050, 14, 51, 510, 'Hidimba Devi Temple', 'Set amidst towering deodars with blue-flowered hydrangeas in bloom, this is Manaliâ€™s most famous temple. As the name suggests, the temple (which dates back to 1533 and was built by Maharaja Bahadur Singh) is dedicated to the demoness Hadimba Devi, of Mahabharat fame. Hadimba, who married Bheem and gave birth to their son Ghatotkacha, is supposed to have stayed back.', '1468481501Hidimba Devi Temple.jpg', '1468481501Hidimba Devi Temple2.jpg'),
(1051, 14, 51, 508, 'Solang Valley', 'Solang Nala (Valley) derives its name from combination of words Solang (Nearby village) and Nullah (water stream). It is a side valley at the top of the Kullu Valley in Himachal Pradesh, India 14 km northwest of the resort town Manali on the way to Rohtang Pass, and is known for its summer and winter sport conditions. The sports most commonly offered are parachuting, paragliding, skating and zorbing.', '1468481530Solang Valley.jpg', '1468481530Solang Valley2.jpg'),
(1052, 14, 51, 510, 'Manikaran Gurudwara', 'It was a unique experience as this place is situated next to hot water springs which have boiling water. There is a peaceful feeling in this place. The langar has never used a fire. All the food is cooked in the spring and it is amazing. Just feel close to God when you have warm springs water to bath and river flowing around this gurdwara .you feel in heaven with beautiful surroundings around and calmness of the place.\r\n\r\n', '1468481564Manikaran Gurudwara.jpg', '1468481564Manikaran Gurudwara2.jpg'),
(1053, 14, 51, 510, 'Manikaran Gurudwara', 'It was a unique experience as this place is situated next to hot water springs which have boiling water. There is a peaceful feeling in this place. The langar has never used a fire. All the food is cooked in the spring and it is amazing. Just feel close to God when you have warm springs water to bath and river flowing around this gurdwara .you feel in heaven with beautiful surroundings around and calmness of the place.\r\n\r\n', '1468481632Manikaran Gurudwara.jpg', '1468481632Manikaran Gurudwara2.jpg'),
(1054, 15, 52, 509, 'Apharwat Peak', 'This is where dreams come true. Dont stop at phase1.. go to Phase 2 if u wanna experience solitude. Climb as much as u can once u get down from the gondola and walk up to place where there is less crowd. Take in the scenery and feel at home. This is where u lose your  heart.', '1468481684Apharwat Peak.jpg', '1468481684Apharwat Peak2.jpg'),
(1055, 15, 52, 509, 'Gulmarg Gondola', 'Gulmarg Gondola in Gulmarg, Jammu and Kashmir is the world''s second highest operating cable car. It was amazing ride and the skiing & sledging at the top was fun. Brilliant view of the snow covered mountains and freaky weather further added to the charm. Its an awesome experience. Yes the line and the guides give u a headache. But once inside the gondola all ur irritation will turn into excitement. Worth a do. Go for it.', '1468481713Gulmarg Gondola.jpg', '1468481713Gulmarg Gondola2.jpg'),
(1056, 15, 53, 510, 'Vaishno Devi', 'Vaishno Devi, also known as Mata Rani, Trikuta and Vaishnavi, is a manifestation of the Hindu Mother Goddess Mahalakshmi. The words "maa" and "mata" are commonly used in India for "mother", and thus are often used in connection with Vaishno Devi.Vaishno Devi Mandir (Hindi: à¤µà¥ˆà¤·à¥à¤£à¥‹à¤¦à¥‡à¤µà¥€ à¤®à¤¨à¥à¤¦à¤¿à¤°) is a Hindu temple dedicated to the Hindu Goddess, located in Katra at the Trikuta Mountains within the Indian state of Jammu and Kashmir. Definitely it''s great place of holiness and divinity, when you came to such a place, you could realize the power of goddess. ', '1468481744Vaishno Devi.jpg', '1468481744Vaishno Devi2.jpg'),
(1057, 15, 54, 509, 'Indira Gandhi Tulip Garden', 'Indira Gandhi Memorial Tulip garden previously Model Floriculture Center is a tulip garden in Srinagar, India. It is the largesttulip garden in Asia spread over an area of about 12 hectares.[2] It is situated on the foothills of Zabarwan Range with an overview ofDal Lake. The garden was opened in 2007 with the aim to boost floriculture and tourism in Kashmir Valley.', '1468481785Indira Gandhi Tulip Garden.jpg', '1468481785Indira Gandhi Tulip Garden2.jpg'),
(1058, 15, 54, 504, 'Dal Lake', 'Dal lake has been the platform of of performance from time immemorial the que for movie shooting Is still the centre stage of the valley It absorbs and focuses the centre of attraction of the whole city The walk on the banks The shikaras pulsating with life The house boats It is a FLOATING LIFE.', '1468481810Dal Lake.jpg', '1468481810Dal Lake2.jpg'),
(1059, 15, 55, 509, 'Pangong Tso', 'No words are sufficient to define the beauty of this place. I think every one should make a bike trip to this place. Serene lake at the backdrop of snow capped mountain.When I first saw this lovely lake in the movie Three Idiots, I thought it was photoshopped. But when I actually saw this wonderful place, it was like being in a world of untouched beauty. It was like heaven on earth. This lovely lake is absolutely gorgeous with myriad colors and water birds. It is extremely windy and freezing up.', '1468481840Pangong Tso.jpg', '1468481840Pangong Tso2.jpg'),
(1060, 15, 55, 501, 'Khardungla Pass', 'Want to be on top of the world? Then here is your answer. At 18340 Ft height, Khardung La stands strong. Khardungla Pass is claimed to be the highest motor-able road in the world. Biking will be a great thrill. The place is good, cold and windy and also have low oxygen. This heighest motor able road connects Leh to Nubra. Enjoy the height, the snowfall, the thrill of being there.', '1468481867Khardungla Pass.jpg', '1468481867Khardungla Pass2.jpg'),
(1061, 15, 55, 510, 'Shanti Stupa', 'Shantistupa architecture says it''s own beauty by itself as it''s very beautiful and peaceful ,there is a gonpa for Lord budhha and it''s amazingly beautiful , you will feel lot of fresh air when we go up to the stupa . As the name says One will get Shanti-Peace here. One can have 360-degree view of Ladhak and enjoy its serene views.', '1468481894Shanti Stupa.jpg', '1468481894Shanti Stupa2.jpg'),
(1062, 15, 55, 510, 'Thiksey Monastery', 'Thickset Monastery is about 19-20 km from Leh on Manali highway. The strategic placement of its structure at a higher ground with 12 storey construction gives the monastery its typical architectural style. A sitting Bhuddha is placed in the main prayer hall & if you spend little time gazing at the magnificent idol, you''ll feel at peace.', '1468481919Thiksey Monastery.jpg', '1468481919Thiksey Monastery2.jpg'),
(1063, 15, 55, 510, 'Thiksey Monastery', 'Thickset Monastery is about 19-20 km from Leh on Manali highway. The strategic placement of its structure at a higher ground with 12 storey construction gives the monastery its typical architectural style. A sitting Bhuddha is placed in the main prayer hall & if you spend little time gazing at the magnificent idol, you''ll feel at peace.', '1468481963Thiksey Monastery.jpg', '1468481963Thiksey Monastery2.jpg'),
(1064, 16, 56, 510, 'Jagannath Temple', 'This superb spiritually rejuvenating temple complex is located about 10 kms from the main city and located on top of a small hillock which you will barely notice to be very high or steep. Vehicles can go almost to the top and the staircase is also not very difficult to negotiate. The Gopuram is unique. Situated over a hill, one can see through the entire city from the temple.', '1468481988jagannath-temple.jpg', '1468481988Jagannath Temple2.jpg'),
(1065, 16, 56, 509, 'Rock Garden', 'Evenings, with the Kanke dam in the background makes it picturesque. Rock Garden is situated over the hills at Kanke Dam. It is the best place for children & adults who want to enjoy their evening, sundays or weekends.\r\nIt''s one of the most unexpected yet beautiful places in the city.\r\n', '1468482011Rock Garden.jpg', '1468482011Rock Garden2.jpg'),
(1066, 16, 56, 515, 'Dassam Falls', 'The falls are really beautiful and worth going. The best time to visit the falls is in monsson and early winters. While entering the Dasham falls area, there are two ways for going to the fall, take to the left if you want to visit main site, and right for the back side of the fall. While going to fell water at fall, walk carefully, as one may come across wild reptiles including snakes. ', '1468482041Dassam Falls.jpg', '1468482041Dassam Falls2.jpg'),
(1067, 16, 57, 509, 'Jubilee Park', 'This is a gorgeous place celebrating a city and it''s founder. It epitomizes all that is best about the city and shows how industrialization can be sustainable for people and the environment. Beautifully planned and laid out like the city itself, Jamshedpur and Jubilee park is a pleasant surprise. Great for long walks and runs. Excellent place in almost city centre, it can make feel relaxed, rejuvenated with so many flowers, lush green grass and lakes.', '1468482066Jubilee Park.jpg', '1468482066Jubilee Park2.jpg'),
(1068, 16, 57, 504, 'Dimna Lake', 'the dimna lake location is so that it is in the centre of dalma hills and all the water of the hills in the rainy season is collected in the dimna lake. it is the source of water throuthout the year for jamshedpur. also it is very beaytiful and well maintained by Tatasteel. Great place to have a peace, where there is no pollution of air or noise, Feel the beauty of Lake with Mountains.', '1468482091Dimna Lake.jpg', '1468482091Dimna Lake2.jpg'),
(1069, 16, 57, 509, 'Tata Steel Zoological Park', 'This zoo in heart of Jamshedpur offers a diverse wildlife collection. The star attraction includes mandarin ape, lion and tigers. Its well maintained and should offer relaxation for 3-4 hrs. You can see a beautiful butterfly park also inside this. This zoological park is situated on the banks of a beautiful lake.', '1468482118Tata Steel Zoological Park.jpg', '1468482118Tata Steel Zoological Park2.jpg'),
(1070, 16, 57, 509, 'Tata Steel Zoological Park', 'This zoo in heart of Jamshedpur offers a diverse wildlife collection. The star attraction includes mandarin ape, lion and tigers. Its well maintained and should offer relaxation for 3-4 hrs. You can see a beautiful butterfly park also inside this. This zoological park is situated on the banks of a beautiful lake.', '1468482197Tata Steel Zoological Park.jpg', '1468482197Tata Steel Zoological Park2.jpg'),
(1071, 17, 58, 510, 'Mysore Maharajah''s Palace (Amba Vilas)', 'The Palace of Mysore is a historical palace in the city of Mysore in Karnataka, southern India. It is the official residence and seat of the Wodeyars â€” the Maharajas of Mysore, the royal family of Mysore. Mysore is commonly described as the City of Palaces. Mysore Palace is now one of the most famous tourist attractions in India, after the Taj Mahal, and has more than 6 million visitors annually.', '1468658354pala1.jpg', '1468658354pala2.jpg'),
(1072, 17, 58, 509, 'Sri Chamarajendra Zoological Gardens,Mysore Zoo', 'This is by far one of the best zoo in India when it comes to cleanliness, efficiency, organizing the whole thing and well maintained animals. Very educational - the little information boards they have... The well kept pathways are apt for a leisurely walk or if you have kids who like running, well then enjoy the chase! Must do if you''re in Mysore.', '1468482444Sri Chamarajendra Zoological Gardens,Mysore Zoo.jpg', '1468482444Sri Chamarajendra Zoological Gardens,Mysore Zoo2.jpg'),
(1073, 17, 58, 510, 'Somnathpur Temple', 'A must visit for Mysore tourists. The stone carvings are fantastic. Little long drive around 35 km from Mysore but worth it. The site is protected by archaeological survey of India as protected heritage site. You have to pay a small entry fee. Take a guide who can give you the facts and heritage story.\r\nIt was am amazing experience visiting the war-torn, ruined and plundered temple once supposedly to be very rich. on can fel the richness by looking at the destruction left behind by the plunderers.\r\n', '1468482508Somnathpur Temple.jpg', '1468482508Somnathpur Temple2.jpg'),
(1074, 17, 59, 512, 'Badami Cave Temples', 'The color of the stones and the structure of the rocks here itself is sufficient to spellbound one. There are total 4 cave temples. First 3 are having sculptures of Hindu god & goddess and the 4th one is having Mahavir Jain sculptures. The cave temples were cut in the rock with immense care. Wow, this is carved almost hundreds of years back and with their technology. History and art lovers shouldn''t miss this at all.', '1468482540Badami Cave Temples.jpg', '1468482540Badami Cave Temples2.jpg'),
(1075, 17, 59, 510, 'Vithala Temple Complex', 'Vithala Temple is a work of beautiful art and architecture. The weather was wonderful. It is a huge complex with many monuments. To see it detail, it might take 3-4 hrs to finish it. It is advisable to take help of guide, as you might not understand manythings without help. Very picturesque place. One of three stone chariots of India is located here.\r\n\r\n\r\n', '1468482564Vithala Temple Complex.jpg', '1468482564Vithala Temple Complex2.jpg'),
(1076, 17, 60, 517, 'Wonderla Amusement Park', 'Wonderla is one of those few places around Bangalore where you can be entertained non stop and yet when the day ends and it''s time to head back home you feel you still have to have more fun. The moment you enter the premises the energy of the place grows on you and ride after ride you get sucked . Its a must visit place for any coming to bangalore. Even though a little pricy, its worth it!. ', '1468482589Wonderla Amusement Park.jpg', '1468482589Wonderla Amusement Park2.jpg'),
(1077, 17, 60, 510, 'ISKCON Temple Bangalore', 'The Indian Society of Krishna Consciousness has built this magnificent edifice on a hillside .Thousands of pilgrims visit the temple,walk up the steps praying all the while as the need succour from their day to day problems.As they ascend and pass through the portal to the sanctum sanctorium they hear the music of the devotees singing.\r\n\r\n', '1468482614ISKCON Temple Bangalore.jpg', '1468482614ISKCON Temple Bangalore2.jpg'),
(1078, 17, 60, 510, 'ISKCON Temple Bangalore', 'The Indian Society of Krishna Consciousness has built this magnificent edifice on a hillside .Thousands of pilgrims visit the temple,walk up the steps praying all the while as the need succour from their day to day problems.As they ascend and pass through the portal to the sanctum sanctorium they hear the music of the devotees singing.\r\n\r\n', '1468482683ISKCON Temple Bangalore.jpg', '1468482683ISKCON Temple Bangalore2.jpg'),
(1079, 19, 61, 519, 'Kavaratti Island Lagoon', 'Lush blue arabian sea, clear sky giving a contrast to the tilted cocunut trees, nearly calm water. you wont feel you are in india but you are.. During the flight course only you would see how water color changes to blue water. Wonderful travel experience. I recommend everyone must visit it at least once in life time to see this heavenly beauty. Clean,simple and affordable trip with amazing scuba diving experience. ', '1468482721Kavaratti Island Lagoon.jpg', '1468482721Kavaratti Island Lagoon2.jpg'),
(1080, 19, 61, 509, 'Kavaratti Island Marine Aquarium', 'If you want to enjoy marine life. Visit. Corals are amazing here. You can go out 2 km into the sea and still stand waist deep. The corals and fishes are mesmerising. Not to be missed. One gets to see the different types of marine life in these regions. The corals, their shapes and designs are fascinating. One wonders how nature works with precision.', '1468482756Kavaratti Island Marine Aquarium2.jpg', '1468482756Kavaratti Island Marine Aquarium3.jpg'),
(1081, 19, 62, 519, 'Minicoy island', 'Minicoy island has easily the best beach in India and even comparable to that of Maldives, Mauritius !! Crystal clear water and that too just 1m deep till 1km into the sea .. Beautiful corals around the beach which makes snorkeling and scuba diving amazing !! Resort is great, Food served is tasty and has lot of variety. ', '1468482780Minicoy Island.jpg', '1468482780Minicoy Island2.jpg'),
(1082, 19, 62, 519, 'Minicoy island', 'Minicoy island has easily the best beach in India and even comparable to that of Maldives, Mauritius !! Crystal clear water and that too just 1m deep till 1km into the sea .. Beautiful corals around the beach which makes snorkeling and scuba diving amazing !! Resort is great, Food served is tasty and has lot of variety. ', '1468482846Minicoy Island.jpg', '1468482846Minicoy Island2.jpg'),
(1083, 33, 63, 503, ' Charminar', 'The Charminar, constructed in 1591 CE, is a monument and mosque located in Hyderabad, Telangana, India. The landmark has become a global icon of Hyderabad, listed among the most recognized structures of India.[1] The Charminar is situated on the east bank of Musi river.[2] To the west lies the Laad Bazaar, and to the southwest lies the richly ornamented granite Makkah Masjid.[3] It is listed as an archaeological and architectural treasure on the official "List of Monuments" prepared by the Archaeological Survey of India under the The Ancient Monuments and Archaeological Sites and Remains.', '1468482878charminar.jpg', '1468482878char2.jpg'),
(1084, 33, 63, 509, 'Nehru Zoological Park', 'Nehru Zoological Park (also known as Hyderabad Zoo or Zoo Park) is a zoo located near Mir Alam Tank in Hyderabad,Telangana, India. It is one of the most visited destinations in Hyderabad.[3] Zoo hours vary by season, and the zoo is closed on Mondays. Nehru Zoological Park, Hyderabad was established in vide G.O.Ms. No.247, dated 26 October 1959. It was opened to the public on 6 October 1963. The Nehru Zoological Park is run by forest department, Government of Telangana, and is named after the firstprime minister of the country, Jawaharlal Nehru.', '1468482906Nehru Zoological Park.jpg', '1468482906nehru2.jpg'),
(1085, 33, 63, 503, 'Golkonda Fort', 'Golkonda, also known as Golconda or Golla konda ("shepherd''s hill"), is a citadel and fort in Southern India and was the capital of the medieval sultanate of the Qutb Shahi dynasty (c.1518â€“1687), is situated 11 kilometres (6.8 mi) west of Hyderabad. It is also atehsil of Hyderabad district, Telangana, India. The region is known for the mines that have produced some of the world''s most famous gems, including the Koh-i-Noor, the Hope Diamond and the Nassak Diamond.', '1468482950golkonda fort.jpg', '1468482950gol2.jpg'),
(1086, 33, 64, 510, 'BhadrakÄlÄ«  Temple', 'BhadrakÄlÄ« (literally "Good Kali,") is a Hindu goddess popular in Southern India. She is one of the fierce forms of the Great Goddess (Devi) mentioned in the Devi Mahatmyam. Bhadrakali is the popular form of Devi worshipped in Kerala as Sri Bhadrakali and Kariam Kali Murti Devi. In Kerala she is seen as the auspicious and fortunate form of Kali who protects the good.\r\nThis goddess is represented with three eyes, and four, twelve, or eighteen hands. She carries a number of weapons, with flames flowing from her head, and a small tusk protruding from her mouth. Her worship is also associated with the Tantric tradition of theMatrikas as well as the tradition of the ten Mahavidyas and falls under the broader umbrella of Shaktism.\r\n', '1468483023Bhadrakali Temple.jpg', '1468483023bhadra2.jpg'),
(1087, 33, 64, 510, 'The Thousand Pillar Temple', 'The Thousand Pillar Temple or Rudreshwara Swamy Temple is a historic Hindu temple located in the town of Hanamakonda,Telangana State, India. It is dedicated to Shiva, Vishnu and Surya. Many Hindu temples were developed under the patronage of Ganapati Deva, Rudrama Devi and Prataparudra of Kakatiya dynasty. The Thousand Pillar Temple was believed to be constructed during the period between 1175â€“1324 CE by order of the king, Rudra Deva. It stands out to be a masterpiece and achieved major heights in terms of architectural skills by the ancient Kakatiya vishwakarma sthapathis.', '1468483123Thousand Pillar Temple.jpg', '1468483123thousand2.jpg'),
(1088, 2, 2, 519, 'Barren Island', 'Barren Island is located in the Andaman Sea, one of the most easterly islands in the Andaman Islands chain. It is the only confirmedactive volcano in South Asia. Along with the rest of the Andamans, it is a part of the Indian Union Territory of Andaman and Nicobar Islands, and lies about 135 km (84 mi) northeast of the territory''s capital, Port Blair. The first recorded eruption of the volcano dates back to 1787. Since then, the volcano has erupted more than ten times, with the most recent one which started in September 2010 and continued through January 2011.[1]\r\nAfter the first recorded eruption in 1787, further eruptions were recorded in 1789, 1795, 1803â€“04, and 1852. After nearly one and halfcentury of dormancy, the island had another eruption in 1991 that lasted six months and caused considerable damage. There were eruptions in 1994â€“95 and 2005â€“07, the latter considered to be linked to the 2004 Indian Ocean earthquake.\r\n', '1468483207barren1.jpg', '1468483207barren2.jpg');
